<DOC><DOCNO> AP881018-0081 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-10-18-88 1113EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r w PM-DrugHelicopters     10-18 0168</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Drug Helicopters,150</SECOND><HEAD>Pentagon OKs Copter Sale to Colombia</HEAD><DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   The Pentagon notified Congress today it hadapproved the sale of three UH-60 Blackhawk helicopters to Colombiafor use by that South American nation in fighting drug trafficking.   Assuming there are no congressional objections, the DefenseDepartment said it would sell the three copters along with supportequipment, spare parts and pilot training services for $26 million.   ``The sale will enhance the ability of the government ofColombia to interdict the flow of narcotics which make their way tothe United States,'' the Pentagon said.   ``The primary use of these helicopters will be to transportColombian soldiers or police in air mobile operations againstnarcotics traffickers and insurgent forces. These three Blackhawks,in addition to five already in Colombia, will provide Colombiasecurity forces with a significant tactical capability.''   The Pentagon said that the U.S. Army would be responsible foroverseeing the transaction and that the prime contractor would beSikorsky Aircraft of Stratford, Conn.</TEXT></DOC>